              <h3 class="mb-3">Traditional Dress of Nagaland</h3>
              
              <p class="mb-auto">These tribes carry certain folklores depicting the gallant acts of their ancestors. Their costumes aptly display the ancestral lineage. The design of shawl denotes the social status of the wearer. The attire worn by the males include a conical red headgear decorated with Hornbill's black and white feathers and wild boar's canine teeth.</p>
             
